<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-24T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.5151/87: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wright</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-24T13:00:00+01:00">December 24, 1936—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 24—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>62. I am today in receipt through the Foreign Office of a written
                            statement of the National Bank declaring that it now allots and in
                            future will allot exchange for all American goods strictly in accordance
                                <pb facs="0164" n="65" xml:id="pg_65"/> with the provisions of
                            section 2 of supplemental agreement of March 29, 1935.</p>
                        <p>Text of covering note and of foreign statement by mail.<note n="31" xml:id="d34fn31">Neither printed.</note> Written confirmation of
                            such other points as have been satisfactorily resolved to date as
                            reported in my despatches is promised early in January.<note n="32" xml:id="d34fn32">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>